core

Class AbstractRanking

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.AbstractComponent
      • core.AbstractRanking

  • public abstract class AbstractRanking
extends AbstractComponent
    Abstract superclass for ranking/sorting candidates. Rankings are used to sort a list of candidates in a decreasing order of fitness.

    AbstractSingleProblems can only use the AbsoluteRanking component while AbstractMultiProblems can use various more sophisticated algorithms.

    Author:
    Istvan Fehervari

      • sortCandidates

        public abstract int sortCandidates(java.util.ArrayList<AbstractRepresentation> representations,
                 ProblemXMLData problem,
                 NESRandom random)
        Sorts the given array of representations in a descending order of fitness and returns the number of evaluation that was required for the ranking to finish. Evaluation of the candidates is done by the provided problem component.
        Parameters:
        representations - The population to be sorted.
        problem - The problem descriptor to be used for evaluation.
        random - The random generator object used for sorting.
        Returns:
        the number of evaluations that were needed to rank the given set of representations
